   21. 'Just, Vâse*tth*a, as if a man should make a staircase in the
place where four roads cross, to mount up into a mansion. And people
should say to him, "Well, good friend, this mansion, to mount up into
which you are making this staircase, do you know whether it is in the
east, or in the south, or in the west, or in the north? whether it is
high or low or of medium size?'

   'And when so asked, he should answer: "No."

   'And people should say to him, "But then, good friend, you are making
a staircase to mount up into something--taking it for a mansion--which,
all the while, you know not, neither have seen!"

   'And when so asked, he should answer: "Yes."

   'Now what think you, Vâse*tth*a? Would it not

