   24. 'Again, Vâse*tth*a, if this river A*k*iravatî were full of water
even to the brim, and overflowing{1}. And a man with business on the
other siJe, bound for tlle other side, making for the otller side,
should come up, and want to cross over. And he, standing on this bank,
